{"questionId":"9074330","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Two equal positive fixed point charges <em>Q</em> = +44 μC and point P are at the vertices of an&nbsp;equilateral triangle of side 0.48 m.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/05a51095e639d42f99b3f0d9ffbbbb9caa8904e3.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Point P is now moved closer to the charges.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/91cc04b6b524bd421c1490d6ecdb1d4dd46bbbcd.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">A point charge <em>q</em> = −2.0 μC and mass 0.25 kg is placed at P. When <em>x</em> is small&nbsp;compared to <em>d</em>, the magnitude of the net force on <em>q</em> is <em>F</em> ≈ 115<em>x</em>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the period of oscillations of <em>q</em>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>«</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>»</mo><msup><mi>ω</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>115</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>«</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mi>ω</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>»</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>29</mn><mo> </mo><mo>«</mo><mtext>s</mtext><mo>»</mo></math>&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[2]</strong> marks for a bald correct answer.</em></p>\n<p><em>Allow <strong>ECF</strong> for <strong>MP2</strong>.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074330","referenceCode":"21N.2.HL.TZ0.b.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the period of oscillations of q.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena","9.